Anh - Anh
morph
morph1[mɔ:f]
■ noun
1》 Biology each of several variant forms of an animal or plant.
2》 Linguistics an actual linguistic form.
Origin
1940s: from Gk morphē 'form'.
————————
morph2[mɔ:f]
■ verb change smoothly and gradually from one image to another using computer animation techniques.
■ noun an image processed in this way.
Origin
1990s: element from metamorphosis.
